Commentary: Right on the money! A chance straightaway! Miscommunication too! What a way to start a Test match! Southee bowls a length ball around middle, Shan tucks it to the leg side and takes off looking for a single. His partner though does not look interested as he sends him back. Henry from square leg has a shy at the keeper's end but misses it. Masood is lucky there.
A gentle loosener outside off, Masood shoulders arms to this one.
Another length delivery going away from the left-hander, Masood makes a leave.
Length and across the left-hander once again, Shan does not offer a shot to it.
Good length and around off, Masood manages to get bat on ball as he pushes it towards covers.
A maiden to start for Southee! Bowls a length ball around off, Masood watches the ball closely before making a leave. Pakistan and Masood still to open their account.
Boult coming from over the wicket lands one around off and gets it to move away from Ali, Abid there lets it go through to the keeper.
Back of a length ball around middle. A hint of inswing on it as Abid tucks it to square leg off the back foot.
Good length and around off, Ali is aware of his off pole as he lifts his willow to let the ball through.
Another length delivery which is not in the playing zone of Abid, Ali makes a leave.
This time Boult keeps it on a length and it is a bit closer to the sticks as Ali comes right behind that ball and blocks it out.

Good running and an equally good fielding there. Masood and Pakistan are off the mark here. Length and around middle, Shan tucks it through mid-wicket. The fielder there fails to field it cleanly as the ball rolls towards the fence where Daryl Mitchell puts in a dive and saves the ball from going to the fence there. The batsmen get three there.
Length and on middle, Ali tucks it to the leg side and gets a quick single.
Length ball on off, blocked out off the front foot.

OUT! LBW! Masood departs! Tim Southee is the man once again who draws the first blood. Southee goes full and around off. A hint of tail back into the left hander. Masood fails to dig it out as he gets rapped on the boots. There comes an appeal from the bowler and up goes the finger of the umpire. Masood though consults his partner and then signals 'T'. The replays roll in and there comes the Ultra Edge which shows no spike when the bat is near the ball as it is pad first. Now comes the Ball Tracker and it shows that it is pitching in line, the impact is in line and the wickets too are hitting. Masood departs and takes away a review too.
On middle, Ali tucks it through square leg and gets off the mark with a couple.
Length and outside off, left alone.
Outside off, left alone by Azhar. A successful over from Southee comes to an end.
Fuller and on off, Ali drives it straight to the man at mid on.
On a good length but the length is outside off as Abid makes an easy leave.
Another length ball outside off, Abid is happy to leave it for the keeper.
On a good length and around middle, Abid flicks it straight to the man at short mid-wicket.
Length and outside off, Abid lets it be.
FOUR! First one of the match! Fuller and on the pads, Abid flicks it swiftly through square leg as the fast outfield takes it past the fence for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Azhar drives it crisply but finds the cover fielder.
Good length but the line is down the leg side as Azhar lets the ball through.
Length and outside off, watchfully left alone by Azhar Ali there.
Full and outside off, Azhar does not fiddle with it.
Another length delivery bowled outside off by Southee, Azhar leaves it alone.
Full and angled on the pads, Azhar clips it fine towards fine leg and retains the strike with a single.

A huge shout from Boult but nothing from the umpire. Trent bowls it on a length and around off, Azhar who is camping on the back foot is beaten on his defensive push as the ball hits him high on the thigh pad. Boult appeals but the umpire does not entertain it.
Fuller and on off, pushed towards mid off for a quick run by Azhar.
Good length and outside off, Abid taps it to gully.
Length and around off, pushed to the right of the bowler by Abid. Boult fields it.
BEATEN! Lovely piece of bowling! Boult bowls it on a length and around off, Abid looks to force it off the back foot but the ball straightens a bit and sneaks past the outside edge.
On a length on off, kept out by Abid there.
FOUR! Shot! Short and on middle, Azhar swivels and pulls it through mid-wicket. The ball rolls all along the carpet as Azhar fetches a boundary.
Length and swinging away from the right hander, Azhar lets it be.
A yorker from Southee on off, Azhar does well to dig it out.
Good length on leg, Azhar turns it to square leg.

CHEEKY FOUR! Full and outside off, Azhar opens the face of the bat and tries to run it down between the slips and the gully region but the ball goes off his outside edge and into the fence at third man for a boundary.
Full and angled into Azhar, Ali drives it but finds mid on.

A huge shout from Trent but the umpire is unmoved! Length ball pitching on leg and coming into the batsman, Ali looks to defend it but misses it as he gets hit on the knee roll. Boult appeals but the umpire is unmoved. Looked to be pitching outside leg and also the height could be an issue too.
BEATEN! Length and around off, Abid looks to defend it out but gets beaten all ends up as the ball goes past the outside edge.
FOUR! Pure Timing! Full and on the pads, Abid flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a boundary to his name.
Length and outside off, Abid lets it be.
Another length ball outside off, Abid does not play at it.
Good length and around off, Abid defends it out off the front foot this time.
Length ball angled into off, Azhar plays it with a straight bat to mid on.
Length ball shaping away outside off, Ali makes a leave to it.
Fuller and outside off, Azhar is not interested to play at it.
Another outswinger from Southee and another leave for Azhar Ali.
Length ball around off, Azhar drives it to mid on and looks for a run but is sent back by his partner.
Length and around off, Azhar pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and around leg, clipped straight to the man at square leg by Abid.
Length and outside off, Abid comes on the front foot and then makes a leave.
Fuller and around off, Abid punches it towards mid off and looks for a run but the fielder there gets quickly to the ball and cuts off any chance of a run there.
Short of good length outside off, further moving away from Abid as he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length ball but outside off, Abid is a happy man to let that go.
Full and tantalizing the batsman for a drive, Abid does not fall for it as he shoulders arms to it.
Fuller from Boult too, Azhar does not fall for the trap as he makes a leave.
FOUR! Beautiful drive! Fuller and around middle, Azhar maintains his balance as he drives it all along the ground through mid on and fetches a boundary.
Length ball around off, Azhar looks to drive it through the off side but the ball takes the inner half of the bat and goes towards mid-wicket.
Length ball on off, pushed to mid on.
Outswinger on a fuller length, Azhar lifts his bat and makes a leave.
A dot to end! Length and around off, Azhar is not going to fiddle with away going deliveries as he lets it be.
Length ball from Kyle to start with as Abid strokes it to mid off.
BEATEN! Short of good length with some extra bounce from Jamieson. It is outside off as Abid looks to push it to the off side but is lucky to not have edged that one.
Fuller outside off, Abid pushes it to mid off.
BEATEN! Another length ball which is outside off, Abid comes on the front foot and looks to defend it out but the ball goes past the outside edge and into the mitts of the keeper.
Fuller and around off, Abid looks to defend it out but the ball takes the outside edge and rolls between point and gully. The batsmen take a couple of runs.
Length and outside off, Abid looks to defend but is beaten to get hit on the pads. Nothing from the bowler. A good start for Jamieson there.
Bumper on leg, Azhar watches it and then ducks under it.
Now a length ball which is outside off, Azhar does not offer a stroke to it.
Southee strays one on middle and leg, Azhar flicks it towards fine leg and gets a single.
Full and straight on off, Abid brings the straight drive out as he drives it through mid on. Though the timing is not there on it to reach the fence, the batsmen get three there.
Length and on off, kept out off the back foot.
Length ball on the pads, Azhar tucks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Length ball on off, defended to covers by Azhar.
EDGY FOUR! Full and on off, Azhar looks to push it from within the crease but the ball takes the outside edge and flies past the diving gully fielder. The ball races to the third man fence there.
FOUR! Nicely done! Length and angled into the batsman, Azhar clips it handsomely through backward square leg as the ball races to the fence there.
Length and outside off, Azhar lets it be.
Length ball swinging into the batsman, Azhar looks to play at it but is beaten all ends up.
Length and outside off, Azhar makes a leave.
Good length delivery on off, Abid defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length on off, Abid looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It falls safely ahead of the gully fielder. The batsmen cross ends.
Length ball outside off, Azhar offers no shot to this one.
Good length delivery outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to this one.
Length delivery on off, Azhar pushes it towards point for a run.
Back of a length on off, Abid punches it through point for a couple.
Length ball outside off, Azhar leaves it alone.
Full delivery on off, Azhar keeps it out.
Back of a length on off, Azhar defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to this one.
Bouncer outside off, Azhar sways away from it.
Outside off, Azhar lets it go.

EDGED AND FOUR! Abid is lucky there. Full delivery on off, Abid is lured into the drive as gets an outside edge. It goes past the diving gully fielder and the ball goes towards third man for a boundary. 50 up for Pakistan!
Full again on off, Abid drives it to covers.
Good length delivery on off, Abid defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length on off, Abid blocks it well.
Length delivery outside off, Abid offers no shot to this one.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Good length ball on off, Abid looks to defend but gets hit high on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head. Looks like there was an inside edge on that. Yes, the replays confirm it.
Length ball outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to this one.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Azhar looks to defend but misses it due to the seam movement on this one.
Length delivery on off, Azhar pushes it towards point for a quick single.
Full and outside off, Abid does not bother to play at that.
Back of a length on off, Abid blocks it off the front foot.
Full on middle, Abid flicks it through square leg for a single.
BEATEN! Full and outside off, Abid looks to drive but misses it.

Another LBW appeal turned down by the umpire. Length delivery on middle, Abid looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal from Henry but umpire Chris Gaffaney shakes his head. Definitely going down leg this time though.

Bouncer on middle, Abid does well to duck under it. It goes towards the keeper where Watling jumps and tries to stop it with one hand but it goes over him. The batsmen take a bye. 50-run stand comes up between these two.
Good length ball outside off, Azhar offers no shot to this one.
Full on middle, Azhar flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Length delivery on middle, Azhar flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Class shot! Full delivery on off, Azhar comes on the front foot and presents the full face of the bat as he drives it through covers for a boundary.
Back of a length outside off, Azhar leaves it alone.
EDGY FOUR! Lucky runs there! Length delivery outside off, Azhar guides it with soft hands  past gully as the ball rolls towards third man for a boundary.
Back of a length on middle, Azhar flicks it towards square leg for a run.
Good length ball on off, Abid keeps it out.

OUT! CAUGHT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Jamieson it is once again who strikes for the Kiwis when they needed it. Kyle lands one around off and on a length as he went wide off the crease there. Abid comes forward and looks to push it but unfortunately he gets an outside edge that flies towards second slip where Tim Southee takes the catch. Pakistan lose both their openers.
Full delivery on middle, Azhar flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen get three runs.
Good length ball outside off, Sohail offers no shot to this one.
Full on middle, Sohail flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Full delivery on off, Ali drives it to covers.
Back of a length on off, Azhar looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes safely towards the off side.
Outside off, Azhar leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Lovely shape away from the left hander there! Full delivery outside off, Sohail looks to drive but misses it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Confusion leads to the downfall! Sohail's poor outing on this tour continues as he fails once again with the bat. Jamieson seems to have created a magic out there with the ball as whenever he comes onto bowl he makes sure to get a wicket. Once again he lands one around off and gets it to angle away from Haris, Sohail there is in two minds whether to leave or play. In the end, he is late to decide as the ball takes the cue-end of the bat and flies towards gully where Henry Nicholls takes the catch.
Full delivery on off, Alam plays it to covers.
BEATEN! Nice shape on this one! Length delivery outside off, Alam looks to defend but misses it.
BEATEN! Back of a length outside off, Alam looks to play inside the line of the delivery but misses it.
Full on off, Alam pushes it towards the off side.
Length delivery on leg, Azhar looks to flick but gets it off the pads. It goes towards the leg side. The batsmen take a leg bye.
Full on middle, Alam flicks it through square leg for a run.
Back of a length on middle, Azhar pushes it to mid on.

FIVE WIDES! Bonus runs and Pakistan will take it anyhow. Henry bowls a bouncer, Azhar ducks under it. The ball flies towards the keeper where Watling puts in a leap but the ball just brushes his gloves on its way to the third man fence as the umpire later signals it a wide.
Good length delivery outside off, Azhar lets it go.
On off, Azhar defends it out.
Back of a length on off, Azhar blocks it off the back foot.
Full on middle, Alam flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full again on middle, Alam flicks it through square leg for a single.
Length delivery outside off, Azhar leaves it alone.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Full on middle, Ali drives it through mid on for a boundary.
Length ball on middle, Azhar looks to flick but gets it off the pads. It goes towards fine leg. The batsmen take a leg bye.

OUT! CAUGHT! A ripper from Jamieson consumes Fawad Alam. A well-directed short ball targetting the batsman, Alam who is glued on the back foot looks to get out of the line of fire but fails to do so. The ball takes the gloves and flies towards Watling who accepts the catch gleefully. Pakistan in deep trouble as they lose their 4th wicket.
Length delivery on off, Azhar pushes it to covers.

FOUR! 50 for Azhar Ali! It has been a fine innings from him! With wickets falling at the other end, Azhar has done well to hold one end up as he looks for a partnership to revive the Pakistan innings. Full delivery on middle, Ali drives it through mid on for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Azhar offers no shot to this one.
Back of a length outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to this one.
Full on middle, Azhar flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, Rizwan lets it go.
Full delivery outside off, Azhar offers no shot to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Ali defends it off the back foot.
Bouncer on middle, Ali does well to duck under it.
Back of a length on middle, Azhar looks to flick but misses it and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Length ball outside off, Ali offers no shot to this one.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Ali looks to defend but misses it. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!
FOUR! What a start after lunch! Full and around off from Southee, Rizwan drives it through the ground past mid on and the ball races to the long on fence for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Rizwan does well to keep it out.
Good length and around off, Rizwan blocks it out off the back foot.
Fuller and angled into the pads, Rizwan clips it in the gap between mid on and mid-wicket to get a couple of runs.
Now clips this fuller one through mid-wicket and gets a single does Azhar.
On off, watchfully kept out off the back foot to see off the over from Southee.
FOUR! Driven beautifully! Slightly overpitched around off, Rizwan leans into the shot and creams the drive past mid off and into the fence at long off for a boundary.
FOUR! Consecutive hits to the fence! Short and width on offer, Rizwan waits for the ball to arrive as he cuts it past point and into the fence behind for a boundary. 100 up for Pakistan!
FOUR! Three in a row! Fuller and outside off, Rizwan gets sucked into the drive as he goes with hard hands on it. The ball flies off the outside edge and past the gully fielder for a boundary.

FOUR LEG BYES! Now, Southee strays one on the pads of Rizwan and he just comes inside the line of the ball and clips it fine towards fine leg and bags another boundary. The ball though went off his thigh pads as the umpire signals it as leg byes.
Fuller once again, Rizwan drives it through covers but this time could manage just a brace.

BEAUTY! This is what Trent needs to do. Bowls a length ball around off, gets it to straighten it off the surface as Rizwan is beaten on a tentative push. The ball sneaks through the outside edge of his bat there.
Good length delivery on off, Azhar defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Ali drives it to mid on.
Back of a length outside off, Ali offers no shot to this one.
Length delivery outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to this one.
Length ball outside off, Ali leaves it alone.
Outside off, Ali lets it go.
Fuller and around off, Rizwan comes on the front foot and then blocks it out.
Length ball on off, Rizwan blocks it out to the bowler.
Length delivery outside off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
FOUR! Terrific shot! Back of a length on off, Rizwan punches it through point for a boundary.
Full delivery on middle, Rizwan pushes it to mid on.
BEATEN! Full and outside off, Rizwan looks to drive but misses it.
Length and around off, Ali taps it to covers off the front foot.
Length and outside off, Azhar makes a leave this time.
Length ball on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Another length ball that is outside off and Azhar does not have any fuss to make a leave.
Good length angled into the pads, Azhar tucks it to the man at mid-wicket.
Fuller and on middle, pushed towards mid on off the front foot.
Length and on off, Rizwan taps it off the back foot towards covers.

NOT OUT! Rizwan survives as New Zealand lose their review. Brilliant ball from Boult there. Trent lands one on off and it cuts Rizwan into half as he looks to defend it. The ball though goes between the bat and pad and over the stumps as the keeper collects it. Watling there goes up in an appeal but the umpire does not give it in. Williamson after thinking over decides to review when only 2 seconds were left for the timer to go off. The replays roll in and there comes the Ultra Edge. It shows a flat line when the ball goes past the bat. The onfield call stands as Rizwan survives.
Length ball on leg, tucked towards square leg for a single.
Fuller and around off, Azhar guides it through gully and gets a couple.
Another length ball on the pads, Ali tucks it to the leg side for a single.
A single to end! Length and on the pads, Rizwan turns it towards square leg and retains the strike with  a single.
Full delivery on off, Rizwan drives it back towards the bowler.
Length ball outside off, Rizwan offers no shot to this one.
Full on middle, Rizwan flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Back of a length outside off, Ali shoulders arms to this one.
Length delivery on off, Azhar punches it through point. The batsmen get three runs.
Outside off, Rizwan lets it go.
Length ball outside off, Azhar watches the ball go past him and into the mitts of the keeper.
Another length ball outside off and Azhar once again does not disturb the trajectory of the ball.
Another length ball angled across off, Azhar takes a stride forward and then shoulders arms to it.
Length delivery around off, Azhar drives but finds mid on.
Another length delivery on off, Azhar comes right behind the line of the ball and keeps it out.
Outside off, left alone.

EDGY FOUR! Lucky Rizwan and lucky runs! Fuller and around off, Rizwan pushes it off the back foot but manages to get a thick outside edge that flies through gully and into the third man fence for a boundary.
Length and outside off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
Length and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Good length and outside off, Rizwan sees it and then decides to not play at it.

A mixup but in the end everything is safe. Length ball on off, Rizwan taps it towards point and takes off for a quick single. The fielder there misfields but gathers the ball to have a shy at the bowler's end. He though misses it as the batsmen get a single.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Azhar.
Length ball shaping into the batsman, Rizwan flicks it to mid on. A single taken.
Length ball on off, Azhar taps it to the off side and gets a single. 50-run stand is also up between the two.
Slants on across the right hander, Rizwan lets it go through to the keeper.
Length ball angled into Rizwan, Mohammad there looks to tuck it to the leg side but gets beaten to wear the blow on the thigh pad. The ball rolls to the leg side.
Good length and outside off, Rizwan does not want to play at it.
Another beauty from Boult! Length ball outside off, swinging into the batsman, Rizwan looks to drive it away from the body but gets beaten altogther.
Length and on off, tapped to point.
Length and swinging outside off, Azhar does not offer shot to it.
On a length on off, pushed to covers.
Fuller length ball going away from off, Azhar lets it be.
Outswinger outside off, Azhar leaves it for the keeper.
Short of good length ball down leg, Azhar looks to flick it but misses it as the keeper collects it.
Fuller and on middle, Rizwan clips it to the leg side.
Length ball on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Short ball on middle, Rizwan goes for the pull but is early into the stroke. The ball just lobs over the fielder at mid-wicket as the batsmen cross ends.
Good running between the wickets! Length ball on the pads, Ali clips it through square leg. By the time the ball gets fielded in the deep the batsmen cross for three runs.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball outside off, Rizwan leaves it for the keeper.
Length ball on the pads, Azhar flicks it to the leg side.
Short ball on off, Azhar ducks under it. Watling behind the wicket is just superb.
Length and outside off, Azhar makes a leave.
Good length ball on off, pushed of the back foot.
Length ball on off, tucked off he back foot for a single.
Outside off, left alone..
Full and outside off, Rizwan drives it to covers.
BEATEN! Short and outside off, Rizwan looks to cut but misses it.
BEATEN! Full and outside off, Rizwan looks to drive but misses it.
Short delivery on off, Rizwan keeps it out.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Rizwan looks to drive but misses it.
Outside off, Rizwan offers no shot to this one.
Full on middle, Ali flicks it through square leg for a single.
Good length delivery on off, Rizwan defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Full delivery on off, Rizwan looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Rizwan blocks it off the back foot.
Back of a length on off, Rizwan keeps it out.
Length delivery on off, Rizwan offers a solid defense on this one.
Full delivery on middle, Azhar pushes it towards mid on for a quick single.
Length ball on off, Rizwan pushes it through mid off for a single.
Short of a length delivery, Azhar looks to hop but misses it to get hit near his face.
Full delivery on middle, Azhar flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Rizwan looks to defend but misses it.
Back of a length on off, Rizwan defends it towards point for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Rizwan flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Good length ball on off, Ali defends it off the back foot.
Short delivery on middle, Ali pulls it through mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Good shot! Full delivery on off, Rizwan drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Full delivery on off, Rizwan looks to drive but gets an inside edge on it.
Full again on off, Rizwan drives it through covers. The batsmen get three runs.
FOUR! Beautiful drive to bring up the milestone! 50 for Rizwan! Full and around off, Rizwan leans and drives it through mid off and gets a boundary.
Length and angled into middle, Rizwan fends it awkwardly to the leg side.
Fuller and outside off, Rizwan plays the free flowing drive but finds mid off.
Another fuller one on off, pushed to mid off once again.
Short of good length outside off, Rizwan initially looks to defend it out but seeing the ball rise he drags his back inside the line of the ball.
Jaffa! Length and around off, Rizwan gets squared up as he looks to defend it off the back foot. The ball goes past the outside edge. A testing over from Jamieson comes to an end.
Length and on off, pushed to covers.
Short of good length outside off, further going away, Azhar leaves it.
Fuller on the pads, Azhar clips it towards mid-wicket and gets a couple this time.
Length and on off, tapped to gully this time.
Fuller and on off, Azhar does well to block it out to mid off.
Another good length ball on off, Azhar comes on the front foot and then defends it out.
Full delivery on off, Rizwan drives it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Good shot! Back of a length on off, Rizwan swings hard and places the cut through point for a boundary.
Outside off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
Good length delivery on middle, Rizwan defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short delivery on middle, Rizwan pulls it through square leg for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pakistan lose half their side! An important stand is broken and it is that man Jamieson again. Rizwan was looking flawless till the time Kyle bowled this delivery. He lands on a length and around off, gets it to straighten off the surface a bit. Rizwan looks to defend it out but fails to get behind the line of the delivery as the outside edge flies at a good height towards BJ Watling who does not drop such catches. 88-run stand finally gets broken.
Length delivery on middle, Ali flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Back of a length outside off, Ashraf leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Ashraf offers no shot to this one.
Length delivery on off, Ashraf blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Full ball on off, Ashraf drives it through point for a boundary.

EDGED AND DROPPED! That should have been taken. It is a regulation catch at first slip where Taylor drops it. A fuller length ball angled across the left hander, Ashraf goes for the drive without any footwork. The outside edge is found as it flies towards first slip. Taylor there is late to react as the ball pops out of his hands and gets grassed. Ashraf gets a lifeline. Can he cash on it?
Good length delivery on off, Ali defends it off the back foot.
Length ball outside off, Azhar offers no shot to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Ali flicks it through square leg for a couple.
BEATEN! Back of a length outside off, Ali looks to defend but misses it due to the seam movement on this one.
Length delivery outside off, Ali shoulders arms to this one.
Sharp inswing on this one! Back of a length just outside off, Ali leaves it alone.
Full and outside off, Ashraf does not bother to play at that.
Length delivery on off, Ashraf punches it to covers.
Back of a length on off, Ashraf keeps it out.
BEATEN! Short and outside off, Ashraf looks to cut but misses it.
Good length ball on off, Ashraf defends it off the back foot.
Length ball on off, Ashraf punches it through covers. The batsmen get three runs.
FOUR! Nice shot! Full delivery on middle, Ashraf flicks it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good length delivery on middle, Ashraf defends it out.
Back of a length on off, Ashraf keeps it out.
Outside off, Ashraf offers no shot to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Faheem flicks it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short delivery on middle, Ashraf pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Ali looks to defend but misses it.
Length delivery outside off, Azhar offers no shot to this one.
Back of a length on off, Azhar defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Ali flicks it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! Good shot! A cheeky one though! Length delivery on off, Azhar looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It flies past gully towards third man for a boundary. It was played with such soft hands that the ball rolled between the third slip and the gully fielders. Nicely done despite getting squared up a little bit.
FOUR! Nice shot! Full delivery on middle, Ali drives it through mid on for a boundary.
Length delivery on off, Ashraf defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length on off, Ashraf blocks it well.
FOUR! Nicely played! Overpitched on off, Ashraf drives it with the straightest of the bat and sends it down the ground for a boundary. 200 comes up for Pakistan.
Back of a length on off, Ashraf punches it through covers for a single.
Full on middle, Ali flicks it towards fine leg for a run.
Short ball outside off, Ashraf looks to pull but misses it.
Full delivery on off, Ali looks to drive but gets an outside edge. It goes wide of gully towards third man. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs.
Good length delivery on off, Ashraf blocks it off the front foot.
An appeal for LBW but turned down by the umpire! Back of a length on off, Ashraf looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.

Another appeal and once again the umpire is not interested! Full delivery on middle, Ashraf looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head. It goes towards the leg side. The batsmen take a leg bye.
Outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to this one.
Full on off, Ali pushes it to mid on.
Length ball on off, Ashraf keeps it out.
Back of a length on off, Ashraf defends it off the front foot.
Short delivery outside off, Ashraf looks to pull but misses it.
FOUR! Terrific shot! Back of a length on off, Ashraf guides it through point for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Ashraf defends it off the back foot.
BEATEN! Lovely piece of bowling, nice shape on that one too. Length delivery outside off, Ashraf looks to defend but misses it.
Bouncer on middle, Azhar Ali does well to duck under it.
Bouncer on leg this time, Ali ignores it.
Short of a length on middle, Ali flicks it through square leg for a single.
Down the leg side, Ashraf looks to flick but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, Ashraf defends it off the back foot.
BEATEN! Back of a length outside off, Ashraf looks to defend but misses it due to the seam movement on this one.
Good length delivery on off, Ali defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length outside off, Azhar leaves it alone.
FOUR! Into the 90s goes Azhar Ali! A touch straighter from Boult on the pads, Ali comes inside the line of the delivery and then clips it towards fine leg to fetch a boundary.
Full delivery on middle, Ali flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on off, Ali keeps it out.
Outside off, Ali leaves it alone. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1!
Fuller length ball on off, Ashraf blocks it out back to the bowler.
Another fuller one on middle, Ashraf strokes it to mid on.
This time again it is fuller and around off, Faheem looks to play the off drive but the ball goes off the inner half towards mid on.

A JAFFA! Southee you beauty from where do you get the ball to nip in and out. This one lands on a length and just outside off, Ashraf looks to defend it out but fails to do so. Lucky for him the ball went past his outside edge.
Length and on off, blocked off the front foot.
Fuller on off, driven to covers for a dot. A maiden to start the final session of Day 1.
Fuller length ball across the right hander, Ali shoulders arms to it.
Short of good length ball on off, Ali defends it right near his boots.
Length and across off, Azhar lifts his willow and lets the ball pass.
Fuller outside off, Ali drives it straight to the man at covers.
Another length ball slanted across off, Ali lets it be.
BEAUTY! Length and across the right hander, Ali comes on the front foot and looks to punch it through the off side but is lucky to not have edged one behind to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller and on off, Ashraf taps it off the inner half of the bat towards mid-wicket.
Length ball around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller and outside off, Ashraf drives it handsomely but fails to get it to the fence. The batsmen gets a couple though.
Length ball angled across Faheem, Ashraf shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, Faheem leaves it alone.
On a length and around off, Ali blocks it out back to the bowler.
Short and wide outside off, width on offer as Ali cuts it through cover-point for a single.
Slanting across Faheem, Ashraf does not play at it.
Sweetly timed! Fuller and around off, Faheem punches it through covers and gets a couple this time.
Short and on middle, Ashraf pulls it through square leg and gets a couple.
Length ball on off, defended out.
Length and swinging away from Ali, Azhar leaves it.
Length ball on off, Ali looks to push it off the back foot towards the off side but the ball takes the inside edge and goes to the leg side for a single.
On off, defemded.
Short of length ball on off, Ashraf punches the ball off the back foot towards covers.
Another fuller length ball driven towards covers .
Outside off, played towards mid off this time.
Good length ball outside off, Azhar offers no shot to this one.
Short delivery on middle, Azhar pulls it through mid-wicket for a single.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Ashraf looks to defend but misses it.
Full delivery on off, Ashraf drives it back towards the bowler.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Ashraf looks to defend but misses it due to the seam movement on this one.
BEATEN AGAIN! Back of a length outside off, Ashraf looks to play inside the line of the delivery but misses it.
Length delivery outside off, Ali offers no shot to this one.

OUT! CAUGHT! Heart break for Azhar Ali as he departs in nervous 90s. Delight for Matt Henry, he finally gets a wicket to his name. A brilliant innings from Azhar comes to an end. Henry bowls smartly around length and keeps it on off, Azhar who is camping on the back foot looks to defend it out but the ball just about moves away and takes the outside edge there. The ball flies towards first slip where Ross Taylor this time does not make any mistakes as he gobbles it up.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Gohar looks to defend but misses it. It goes towards the keeper where he fails to stop the ball and concedes a bye.
Back of a length on off, Ashraf punches it through covers for a run.
Length ball on off, Gohar defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Gohar leaves it alone.
Length and outside off, blocked out solidly by Ashraf.
Another length ball around off, kept out towards covers by Faheem.
This time Ashraf blocks this back of a length ball off his back foot to the off side.
Fuller on middle, driven through mid on as Ashraf takes a single.
BEATEN! Back of a length ball outside off, Gohar looks to lay bat on ball but fails to do so.
Short of good length on middle, Gohar hops and keeps it out to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Ashraf looks to defend but misses it.
Back of a length ball on off, Ashraf blocks it off the back foot.
Swing and a miss! Short and outside off, Faheem swings hard on the cut but fails to get anything behind that shot. The keeper does the rest.
Full delivery on middle, Ashraf flicks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length on off, Ashraf defends it off the front foot.
Length ball on off, Ashraf pushes it to covers.
BEATEN! Fuller length ball angled across the left hander, Gohar throws the kitchen sink at it but is beaten there.
Length delivery on off, Gohar pushes it to the off side.
Fuller once again around off, Gohar plays it to gully.
FOUR! First runs in international cricket! Fuller and outside off, Gohar drives it with an open faced bat through gully and point and gets off the mark with a boundary.
FOUR! Handsomely done! Strays one down the leg side this time as Gohar clips it towards fine leg and bags another boundary.
On off, kept out to covers.
PLAY AND A MISS! Short and wide outside off, Ashraf throws the bat at it but fails to get anything on that shot as he gets beaten comprehensively.
Fuller and on off, Ashraf punches it to covers.
FOUR! Glorious! Fuller and outside off, Ashraf drives it straight down the ground and gets a boundary. Glorious swing of the bat there.
Fuller outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Pulled away! Henry serves a short ball on middle which sits nicely for Ashraf to rock on the back foot and pull it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Overpitched  on off, Faheem drives it but finds the bowler at the other end.
Good length delivery on off, Gohar defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length on off, Gohar keeps it out.
Length ball on off, Gohar pushes it to point.
Back of a length outside off, Gohar leaves it alone.
Short ball outside off, Gohar shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, Gohar lets it go.
Length ball outside off, Ashraf offers no shot to this one.
FOUR! Ashraf brings out another drive from his bag of straight drives! Full on middle, slightly overpitched, Ashraf drives it through mid on for a boundary. 250 up for Pakistan!
Back of a length outside off, Ashraf offers no shot to this one.
Full delivery on off, Ashraf drives it to mid off.
Full again on off, Ashraf drives it through covers for a couple.
Length delivery on middle, Ashraf pushes it to mid on.
Full delivery outside off, Gohar looks to drive but misses it.
BEATEN! Back of a length outside off, Gohar looks to defend but misses it.
Full on middle, Gohar flicks it to short leg.
Length delivery on off, Gohar defends it out.
Back of a length outside off, Gohar leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Gohar looks to defend but misses it due to the seam movement on this one.
Length delivery outside off, Ashraf offers no shot to this one.
Back of a length on off, Faheem defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Ashraf drives it to mid on.
Good length ball outside off, Ashraf leaves it alone.
Yorker on off, Ashraf digs it out to covers.
Short ball outside off, Ashraf shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Nice shot! Full delivery on off, Gohar drives it through covers for a boundary.
Full again on off, Gohar drives it to mid off.
Bouncer on middle, Gohar does well to duck under it.
WIDE! Bouncer on off, Gohar ducks under it. The umpire gives it wide for height.
Full delivery on off, Gohar drives it through covers. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jamieson gets his third 5-wicket haul in Tests. Brilliantly bowled. He has made the ball talk today. He lands one on a fuller length and around off, Ashraf looks to drive it through the off side but the ball goes off his outside edge and towards first slip. Ross Taylor there does not make mistake as he takes the catch. The umpire though take it upstairs as they want to check whether it is a bump ball or not. The replays roll in and it confirms that it was a clean catch. Into the tail now are Pakistan.
Full on middle, Afridi keeps it out.
Length delivery on off, Gohar defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length on off, Gohar pushes it towards point for a single.
Good length ball on off, Afridi keeps it out.
BEATEN! Full and outside off, Afridi looks to drive but misses it.
Back of a length on off, Afridi defends it off the back foot.

Edged and just short! Afridi is lucky there. Southee bowls a length ball around off, and gets it to nip away as Afridi goes chasing after it. He though gets a thickish outside edge which goes towards first slip where Ross Taylor is stationed. Taylor goes for the catch but the ball just drops short of him there.
Length delivery outside off, Gohar leaves it alone.
Short ball outside off, Gohar offers no shot to this one.
Full ball outside off, Gohar drives it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
Bouncer on middle, Gohar does well to duck under it.
Full delivery on middle, Gohar flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Short delivery outside off, Afridi lets it go.
Good length delivery on off, Gohar defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Back of a length on off, Gohar guides it through point for a boundary.
Bouncer on middle, Gohar does well to duck under it.
Full delivery on middle, Gohar drives it to mid on.
Full again on middle, Gohar flicks it through square leg for a single.
Back of a length on off, Afridi blocks it off the back foot.
Length ball on off, kept out off the back foot by Gohar.
Edged but does not carry! Length ball around off, Gohar looks to defend it but instead edges one behind to the slip cordon where it falls short of the fielder.
Length and in line with the stumps, Gohar clips it towards mid-wicket.
Length and outside off, Gohar goes for an extravagant drive but fails to get anything behind that shot. Beaten all ends up.
Length and outside off, this time Gohar does not go chasing a ball which is outside off but ends up leaving it.
Back of a length ball on off, Gohar blocks it solidly from within the crease.
Length and outside off, Afridi plays inside the line and lets the ball through to the keeper.
Full and on off, Afridi looks to drive it through covers but fails to get it in the gap.
Good length delivery outside off, Afridi makes a leave.
Length and outside off, Afridi makes a leave.
Short of length ball on off, Afridi blocks it out.
A half hearted appeal for LBW! Back of a length ball  on off, Afridi catches the ball right between his thighs.
Short of a length ball on off, Gohar plays it to point.
FOUR! Gohar is justifying his selection. Overpitched around off, Gohar drives it through mid off and fetches a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller on off, driven firmly but straight to Jamieson.
Length delivery outside off, Gohar makes a leave now.
Length ball on off, kept out off the back foot by Gohar.
Another edge that falls short of the fielder! Good length delivery on off, Afridi looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards second slip where it falls short of the fielder.
Full delivery on middle, Afridi flicks it through square leg for a single.
Short ball outside off, Gohar looks to pull but misses it.
Bouncer on off, Gohar does well to duck under it.
Short delivery on off, Gohar looks to duck but gets it off the shoulder. The batsmen take a leg bye.
Bouncer on middle, Afridi ducks under it.
Length delivery on off, Gohar blocks it off the back foot.
Back of a length on off, Gohar defends it off the back foot.
Bouncer down the leg side, Gohar does well to duck under it.
Short delivery on off, Gohar looks to defend but gets it off the pads. It goes towards third man. The batsmen take a leg bye.
Good length ball on off, Afridi keeps it out.
Back of a length on off, Afridi defends it to covers.
Length delivery on off, Gohar defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Gohar drives it through mid off. Williamson chases it and does well to stop it just before the ropes. The batsmen get two runs.
FOUR! Short delivery on off, Gohar punches it through point for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! A brilliant innings on debut comes to an end. Southee comes back on and gets a wicket with the second new ball. The trap was set with deep square leg out there. Southee bowls short and around middle, Gohar cannot resist himself from going for the pull shot. He though mistimes it high in the air. Kyle Jamieson there settles under it and takes the catch.
Full delivery on off, Afridi drives it through mid off. The batsmen get three runs.
Back of a length outside off, Abbas offers no shot to this one.
Good length ball on off, Afridi keeps it out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Boult finally gets a wicket! The harder ball gets carried away easily. Good length ball on off, Afridi looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards gully where Nicholls takes a comfortable catch.
FOUR! Nicely played! Length ball on off, Shah punches it through covers for a boundary.
FOUR! Nicely driven! Full delivery on off, Naseem drives it through covers for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Shah defends it off the back foot.
BEATEN! Length delivery outside off, Naseem looks to defend but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, Abbas offers a solid defense on this one.
Bouncer on middle, Abbas does well to duck under it.
Length ball on off, Abbas keeps it out.
Back of a length on off, Abbas defends it off the back foot.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Abbas looks to defend but misses it.
Full on middle, Abbas drives it to mid on.
Good length delivery on off, Shah defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nicely played! Length delivery on middle, Naseem flicks it towards fine leg for a boundary.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Shah looks to defend but misses it due to the seam movement on this one.
BEATEN! Length delivery on off, Naseem looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.

OUT! CAUGHT! That brings the end of Pakistan innings. Boult cleans up the final two wickets. He lands one on a length and gets it to move away from the right hander, Naseem there goes chasing outside off. He though manages to get a thick outside edge which flies towards Latham at second slip who takes the catch with ease. PAKISTAN END WITH 297 AT THE END OF THEIR FIRST INNINGS!
Good length ball outside off, Tom leaves that alone.
Another one in the channel outside off, Latham watchfully leaves that alone.
Outside off, left alone.
Shaheen goes a little wayward this time. It is down the leg side and Tom Latham shoulders arms.
First runs for the Kiwis. Good length ball outside off, Tom pokes it to the off side and takes a single.
Good first over from Afridi. Lands it on a length around off, it pitches and seams in, safe to leave though and Tom does just that.
Good length ball outside off, left alone. 'Great start' is the response from behind the wickets.
In the channel outside off, Latham shoulders arms there.
BEATEN! Oh.... that was close. Wonderful line from Mohammad. Full length ball just outside off, Tom Latham comes forward to have a poke at that but misses.
Oh.... that is some leave from TL. That one was very close to the off pole. Abbas lands it full and around off, it pitches and straightens, as Tom leaves that.
Full and outside off, dabbed to point. Tom enjoys playing on this wicket more.
Full, swinging in, close to off, stabbed through the covers for a single.

Edge.... but does not carry. Flies off to backward point. Length ball close to off, it pitches and bounces. Latham looks to defend but the ball takes the shoulder of his bat and falls safely near backward point.
Off the pads. Good shot. Full and on the pads, flicked to deep square leg. Tom Latham gets three here.
Full and well outside off, an easy leave for Blundell. Shaheen Afridi searching for some swing here.
Good length ball outside off, Tom Blundell lets it be. 'Ahahaha, lovely' say the vistiors' players.
Very full ball around the off pole, dug out to the off side. That is a very good ball from SA. Wonderful shape presentation.
Length delivery outside off, left alone.
Full and on the off pole, blocked.
That is the angle. Full and just outside the off pole line, bunted down to mid on.
Lands it full and around the off stump, it pitches and comes back in. Tom lets that one be. Very close to the off stump there.
An inswinger, outside off, left alone.
Fullish and outside off, Latham leaves it. Leaving well this morning, Tom Latham.
BEATEN! Drawn into the shot, TL. Gets away with that. Full and moving away, outside off, Tom comes forward to defend but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Good length ball outside off, Tom Blundell leaves that for the keeper to collect.
Length ball just outside the off stump line, the right-hander leaves it. SA is trying to bring the ball into the right-hander here.
Full again from Shaheen, outside off, left alone on its way.
On the pads, clipped to short mid-wicket. Still waiting to get off the mark, Tom.
Angles in a good length ball around off from round the wicket, Blundell leaves that. That one came in sharply.
Length delivery just outside the off pole, Blundell jumps and keeps it out on the off side. Shaheen has bowled really well so far, in the morning.
Full and coming into off, with the angle, glanced wide of mid-wicket for a single.
Good length ball well outside off, left alone.
Good length ball outside off, defended to the gully region. Tom Blundell is well out of his crease, looking to negate the movement.
Good length ball just outside the off pole, Tom covers his stumps and keeps it out on the leg side. 14 balls and he is yet to get off the mark.

That has hit the pads. Some interest for the LBW from the cordon, but it results in nothing. Good length ball just outside the off pole line, Tom looks to defend that one but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Full and on the stumps, blocked to the off side. Good forward stride there.
Full and angling into the left-hander, onto middle, defended to the off side. Afridi is pitching it up here.

FOUR! Runs here. Full and outside off, Tom comes forward and drives that through a diving cover fielder. It just about manages to trickle into the boundary, beating a fielder who had given it chase and dived in the end, but to no avail.
Full and angled into the off pole line, Latham closes the face of his bat and works it to short mid-wicket. Bit of aggression there from Mohammad Abbas, at short mid-wicket.
Down the leg side, Latham misses his flick. Rizwan dives to his right but fails to stop that, concedes a bye.
Good length ball just outside off, defended to the off side.
Outside off, left alone there.
Good length ball outside off, Tom lets it be.
Some seam movement there. Good leave. On a length outside off, it pitches and moves in, Latham though, reads it well and lets it be.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and angled in, on off and middle, Tom Latham covers his stumps and fends it out towards mid off.
In the channel outside off, TL leaves it alone there.
Good length ball around off, Tom looks to play at it but misses to get hit near the box. OUCH! He sees the funny side of it though.
Full and just outside off, driven to cover.
FOUR! Pulled away. He is so good there, Blundell. Short ball, around the off pole, Tom Blundell presses forward and back and pulls it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Shaheen Afridi goes short again, pulled again, this time straight to fine leg though. So, just a single.
That is a nice shot. A good off-drive. Angles in a full length ball, close to off, Tom drives that wide of mid off and picks up three this time.
Full and on the off pole, solidly blocked.
Full and just outside off, left alone. New Zealand are 19/0 at the end of 9 overs.
FOUR! Ah... it is a nice shot. A lovely off-drive. Full and outside off, Latham punches it down the ground, wide of mid off, and gets a boundary. This is one of his favourite grounds.
Full and swinging away, outside off, Tom Latham watchfully leaves it alone.
On the pads, clipped to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Pulled away. Pulled away! This is really good batting from Tom Latham. Mohammad goes short, Tom hangs back in his crease and swivel-pulls that to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Good length ball just outside the off pole line, left alone.
Good length ball outside off, Tom leaves that alone. 8 from that over.

FOUR! Ohh... there was an outside edge. Streaky, but it will be a four. Naseem runs in an angles a full length ball on middle and leg, Tom looks to work it to the leg side but ends up getting it off the outside edge. It goes in the gap between the slip cordon and gully and down to third man, for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Blundell was initially interested in playing at that, but then, backs off later on.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and on middle, pushed down to the left of mid on. New Zealand scamper through for one.
Good length ball around off, defended back to the bowler.
Good length ball on off, flicked to mid-wicket for a run.
Full and outside off, driven to cover.
BEATEN! It is a nice bit of bowling. Fullish and seaming away outside off, the left-hander looks to defend that but the ball whizzes past his outside edge.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, blocked.
Full and outside the off pole, Tom covers his stumps and keeps it out. He is well outside his crease here.
Maiden over from Abbas. Fullish and near the off pole line, Latham shuffles across and taps it to the on side.
Good length ball well outside off, left alone.
Another good length ball in the channel outside off, Tom lets it be. Shah has got good speed in the tank.
Length ball outside off, Blundell hops and keeps it out to point.

Good length ball on middle and leg, Blundell closes the face of his bat to work it to mid on. He takes off for a crazy run as it had gone straight to the fielder. Shaheen Afridi picks up the ball and flings a throw to the non-striker's end, but he misses. Would have been close, had he hit.
Leaves this ball on a length.
Worked away. Very strong on his pads, Latham. A comfortable three. Full and on the pads, Tom Latham closes the face of his bat, flicks it through square leg and picks up three here.
Not a good start. Strays on the pads with a fuller one, Tom Latham closes the face of his bat and flicks it through square leg for a single.
Length delivery well outside off, well left by Tom.
Length and outside off, Blundell jumps and keeps it out. New Zealand have batted well so far.
Good length ball outside off, defended to the off side.
Good length ball outside off, left alone. 'Lovely bowling' is the feedback from behind.
Good length ball outside off, solidly defended by Blundell. Well played.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Angles in a full length ball on off, good shot from Tom. He closes the face of his bat and glances it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Good length ball around off, defended to the mid on region. A loud 'no' follows.
Short this time from Naseem, on top of the stumps, Latham sits under it.

Full and angled into the off pole, driven firmly to the right of cover. Shaheen there, dives and keeps it out. That was a great bit of fielding. It was traveling. Hang on..... Naseem has overstepped here. No ball called.
Full and outside off, left alone. 'Well bowled' say the Pakistani players.
Good length ball around the off pole, blocked.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Full and seaming in, from outside off, safe to be left alone and Tom does just that.
Good length ball on off, that one has nipped back and copped Blundell. He looks to play at it but misses and gets hit around the groin.
Length delivery outside off, Blundell hops and taps it to the leg side.
Good length ball around off, solidly blocked. 'Lovely' say the Pakistani players from behind the stumps.
Length delivery around the off pole, solidly fended off. NZ are 41/0.
Short ball but down the leg side, Tom sits under it comfortably. 'Lovely bowling' say Pakistan players from behind.
Back of a length and down the leg side, comfortably left by Latham. Not an area where Naseem should try to be in.
Good length ball angled on off, defended to the off side for one.
Good length ball on the pads, Tom closes the face of his bat, glances it to mid-wicket. Just the single. Good rotation of strike here, by the Kiwis. Will unsettle the bowler.
No ball called. Shah has overstepped again. Full and outside off, Tom leaves it alone.
Full and on the off pole line, Latham looks to work it to the leg side but ends up getting a safe leading edge, through the carpet, to the off side.
On off, blocked to mid on.

A shout for LBW but not given. Full and on the pads, Blundell looks to play at that but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal follows, the bowler is late to join the chorus. But the umpire does not give that. Mohammad Rizwan does not opt to review that. Hmm.... Tom Blundell is batting a long way outside his crease. Replays are in and Ball Tracker shows that it was well down the leg side.
Good length ball outside off, Tom shoulders arms.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball outside off, Blundell blocks it to the off side.
Outside off, left alone. 'Lovely bowling' say Ashraf's teammates from behind.
Length delivery outside off, Tom Blundell covers his stumps and keeps it out.
On a good length and outside off, left alone.
Good length ball outside off, pushed back to Naseem Shah.
FOUR! Good shot. All timing. And another boundary for Tom. Full and outside off, beautiful balance as he comes forward and drives it through the covers for a boundary.
Bouncer on top of the stumps, Latham ducks under it. 'One' for the over, says the umpire.
Good length ball around off, blocked to the off side. A 'no' follows.
Length ball, around off, Tom Latham jumps and fends it out. End of the over. 48/0.
Full and straight, outside off, driven down to mid off.

An appeal for LBW but not given. Good length ball on the off pole line, Blundell looks to play at that but misses and gets hit high on the pads. Mohammad Rizwan ponders and ponders and flashes the 'T'. But guess what, he is too late, as the timer has run out. Replays are in, customarily, and indicate that it would have gone on top of the stumps. Saved a review there, Rizwan.
Outside off, left alone.
EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball outside off, Tom looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes in the gap between slips and gully, down to third man, for a boundary.

OUT! LBW! First wicket down! Exactly what Blundell was trying to negate. The seam movement, by staying outside his crease. Full and on off, Blundell looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal follows but to no avail. This time it is closer and Faheem Ashraf convinces his skipper to take the review, albeit in time. And Rizwan, after some deliberation, takes it. Replays are in and there is no bat there. So, we move straight to the Ball Tracker. THREE REDS.... and Tom Blundell has to walk back.
Outside off, left alone.
Length and outside off, Tom looks to play at it but misses out there.
Length delivery outside off, left alone.
Full and on off, blocked to the on side.

OUT! CAUGHT! Latham is gone. Pakistan have struck again. Brilliant from Haris Sohail. New Zealand are 52/2. Good length ball outside off, Tom hangs his bat outside the line, looking to defend. He though ends up getting it off the outer half. It is uppish and goes to Shan Masood at second slip. He fumbles... but hang on.... hang on.... it goes to first slip off the deflection, where Sohail reacts really well to take the deflection. Everybody then falls on Haris Sohail, in celebration. Brilliant from Pakistan.
Outside off, Ross leaves it alone.
Taylor underway. New Zealand are now 53/2. On the pads, Ross Taylor helps it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Full and outside off, RT lets it be. 'Lovely bowling' say the Pakistan players.
Fullish on middle, Rosco gets across and taps it to mid-wicket for one. He has 2 runs in the 4 balls he has faced already.
Good length ball outside off, Kane defends it.
Outside off, left alone.

Good length ball on the pads, Williamson tucks it to short mid-wicket. Ross looks for a single and comes down, Kane Williamson too comes down a couple of steps, before quickly retracting, to say a loud 'no'.
Full and on the off pole, blocked to mid on. A louder 'no' follows this time around.
Bumper, Taylor sits under it. The umpire says 'Gentlemen, one' to the short ball there.
Length delivery outside off, Ross Taylor leaves it for Mohammad Rizwan to collect.
Good length ball on middle, RT hops and taps it to the leg side.
Good length ball angled into the body, Rosco clips it to mid-wicket and takes a single. Ross does well here. Gets off strike.
Short ball, it is a good ball. Well played. KW moves away from the line of the ball.
Good length ball angled into the off pole line, Kane Williamson is solid in his defence.
Full and outside off, left alone. 'Lovely, lovely' say the Pakistanis from behind the stumps.
Full and outside off, stabbed to the off side for one. Good running. Found the gap. And made the call early.

EDGY FOUR! That was half a chance. Full and outside off, the New Zealand skipper comes forward and goes for the drive but ends up generating an outside edge there. It goes uppish but bounces in front of gully, evades his dive, and gets into the deep backward point fence.
Outside off, Kane leaves it alone.
Length delivery well outside off, Williamson is not tempted to play at that. Lets it be.
Good length ball around off, Kane Williamson is solid in defence. Off the middle of the bat. New Zealand are 60/2 at the end of 24 overs.
Length ball outside off, Ross hops and keeps it out.
Fuller, Taylor finds the gap at cover. Should pick up two, and he does.
Short and outside off, Taylor lets that one be.
Good length ball on the pads, Taylor jumps and keeps it out to square leg.

Play and a miss! Ah... that was the one there. Nicely bowled from Shaheen. Angles it across the right-hander, Ross Taylor does not transfer his weight forward, just throws his hand at it. Misses. Almost nicked it though.

FOUR! Driven straight. Nice way to finish for Ross Taylor and New Zealand ahead of Lunch. RT will feel confident with that shot. Straight down the ground. Full and on the off pole line, Rosco drives it through the ground, wide of the bowler and mid off, and bags a boundary. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2!
Back of a length and on middle, Kane blocks this one out.
First runs of the second session! On middle, worked to the square leg region by Kane.
On a length and on middle, Ross tucks this to the left of the man at fine leg and collects a single.
On off, KW keeps it out nicely.
Outside off, tapped to point. No run on this occasion.
On a length outside off, Williamson raises his blade to let this one through to the keeper.
On middle, nudged to square leg.
Bowls a good length ball around the off pole, Ross pushes it back to the bowler.

EDGED...SHORT! Ross survives. Just what Shaheen was looking to do. On a length and around off, Taylor looked to block this one out but the ball takes the outside edge and goes towards gully but falls just short of the man there.
On off, pushed to covers. Ross wanted the single but was sent back by his skipper.
On off and on a good length, RT blocks this one.

BYE. Woahh...the ball just flew there. A back of a length ball outside off, bounces awkwardly after pitching as RT lets it be. Rizwan tries to dive to get this under control but is not able to. The batters sneak in a bye,
On off, blocked.
On middle, nudged to the square leg region.
Another length ball and this time, around the middle pole, tucked through square leg for a single.
Another length ball on off, KW pushes this one to covers.
Keeps bowling on the good length area and around off and middle, Williamson is aware enough to block this one out solidly.
On off, well kept out. Just one run off the over.
Short of a length and around off, Ross is solid in his defense.
SWING AND A MISS. Shaheen, this time, bowls a short one and this is outside off, Taylor looks to swat this one away but does not connect bat with ball.

Another short of a length delivery, around off, Taylor looking for the block misses and the ball goes into Rizwan's mitts. Shaheen, thinks, that he has his man as he thought there was an edge there but Rizwan says no.
On off, kept out.
On off, Taylor works this to the leg side.
Length and on off, blocked out by Taylor. Maiden by Shaheen, as well.
Outside off, KW lets this one be.
Back of a length and on off, Williamson plays this with soft hands, towards covers.
Another length delivery outside the off pole, Kane does not attempt a shot at this delivery.
On middle, nudged to square leg.
LEG BYE. Down the leg side, KW looks for the tuck away but misses and the ball takes the pad and goes to the left of Rizwan, who dives but spills it. A leg bye is sneaked in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Great bowling by Abbas and he gets his man! Taylor walks back after not doing much and this partnership which could have harmed the visitors comes to a close. Abbas bowls this on a length and around off, nips away slightly after pitching, Taylor is late into the defensive push and can only induce an outside edge. The ball goes towards the slip cordon, where Masood takes a very good catch at second slip. Abbas is pumped up and deservedly so.
Outside off, left alone by Kane.
Bouncer on off, Williamson sways away from the line of the ball.
On a length outside off, Kane is not interested in playing at this.
On a length and around off, Kane pushes this to the mid off region. 'WAITTTTTT', says Kane, for the single.
Short of a length and around off, tapped to point. Again, Kane thinks about the single but then decides not to go.
Another maiden by Shaheen as Kane leaves this good length ball around off alone.
Length on middle, pushed to the leg side.
On off, pushed to the mid-wicket region.
Length ball outside off, Henry leaves this one alone.
On off, well kept out.
Nicholls opens his account for this game! On a length outside off, pushed to the cover region for a single.
Down the leg side, KW misses his flick away.
Bowls this on a length and on the pads, clipped to the right of fine leg for a couple of runs.
On off, pushed to the mid off region. They think about the single but Kane says no, in the end.

NO BALL. This was out but Shaheen has overstepped which will mean that Nicholls survives and gets another life. This is on a length and around off, Henry looks to keep this one out but misses and the ball takes the outside edge and goes to the left of Rizwan, who dives and takes it very nicely. But wait...the umpire's want to check if this is a No Ball and it is. Woah. A good wicket and catch, but disappointment for the visitors.
On middle, blocked.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length and outside off, Henry leaves this one nicely.

EDGED...SHORT! Henry survives again! On a length and around off, Nicholls again looks for the block away but the ball takes the outside edge and goes to the right of gully, who is not able to get his hands under the ball and the ball goes towards the third man region. The batters see this opportunity and sneak in a couple of runs.
On off, well blocked by Kane.
Outside off, Kane leaves this one alone.
In that channel around off and on a good length, Williamson blocks this one out and says 'no' to the single.
On off, pushed towards mid off. 'No', says Kane again, for the run.

FOUR! Williamson plays it late and fetches a boundary! Short of a length and outside off, Kane watches the ball, hops on time and gets on top of the bounce to punch this one through cover-point for a boundary.
On off, blocked out.
Outside off, Henry does not engage on this occasion.
On off, played towards covers for a single.
Length ball outside off, Kane raises his blade to let this one through to the keeper.
Shaheen comes around the wicket this time and bowls a length ball outside off, Kane shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, tapped to point. 1 run off the over.
Outside off, left alone by Henry.

FOUR LEG BYES. Abbas strays from his length and gets punished! Bowls this fuller and on the pads, Henry looks to tuck this one away but misses and the ball takes the pads and goes past the keeper, into the fine leg region for a boundary.
Outside off, Nicholls lets this one be.
On off, pushed to point.
Back of a length on off, Nicholls pushes this back to Abbas.
Length ball outside off, Nicholls punches this one to covers but finds Faheem there.
Length and on off, played towards the point region.
Goes fuller this time, around off, Kane punches this one to the cover region but finds the man there.
Outside off, KW thinks about playing at this, but pulls out at the last moment.
Length and outside off this time, Kane just leaves it.
Back of a length and on off, Williamson pushes this to mid on.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off, Nicholls does not attempt any shot to this one.
Outside off, Henry pushes this to point for a single.
On middle, nudged to square leg for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Length outside off, Nicholls sees no reason to have a poke at this.
Another length ball outside off, another leave by Henry.
On off, KW guides it to gully.
Another length delivery on off, Williamson works this to point and denies the single.
NO BALL. Naseem oversteps and this will be a No Ball. Short of a length and around off, Kane rocks back on his back foot and punches this one through covers to pick up three runs.
On off, blocked out.
Outside off, left alone.
EDGY FOUR! Lucky again, is Nicholls. A short of a length ball on off, Henry looks to block this one out but the ball takes the inside edge and runs away to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, worked to the square leg region.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! Beautifully played by Williamson and he gets a boundary! Overpitches this around off and middle, Kane plays this with a straight bat through the mid on region and the ball runs away to the ropes. 100 up for the Kiwis as well. They still trail by 197 runs.
On middle, KW tucks this one, just past the leg gully fielder, to the fine leg region for one.
On off, blocked out.
Outside off, HN does not engage.
Full and around off, KW pushes it back towards Naseem.
A length delivery on middle, Kane tucks this to mid on and looks for the run but decides not to, in the end.
Short and around off, Kane punches this one through the cover-point region for a brace.
Length and around off, solid push to the gully region by Williamson.
On off, punched to covers.
Short of a length and around off, KW is solid in blocking this one out.
Full and outside off, Henry watchfully sees this one go to the keeper.
Same delivery as the last ball, another leave by Nicholls.
Third delivery in a row which is full and outside off, Henry, again does not think too much in leaving this one alone.
WIDE. Way too short and outside off, Henry leaves it alone. Wided.
BEATEN. Oooohhh....that's a good delivery! Short of a length and around off, Nicholls looks to block this one out but gets beaten.
Full ball again outside off, pushed to covers.
Short of a length and around the middle pole, helped to the fine leg region for a single.
Length on middle, HN pushes it back to Naseem.
Short one around off, Henry, first, was looking to play at that, but seeing the bounce that was generated, thought better and let this one go.
NO BALL. Short one again around off, HN sways away from the line of the ball. Also, Naseem had overstepped and hence, this will be a No Ball.
On off, worked towards the mid on region.
Short one around off, HN, again does not attempt any shot to this.
Short and outside off this time, cut away but finds the point fielder.

What a great last ball! He bowls a yorker on off, Henry sorts his feet out and looks to push at this but misses and the ball whizzes past his outside edge, also past the off pole, into Rizwan's mitts. There is an appeal for caught behind but no says the umpire.
On off, pushed to the leg side.
Length and on off, Kane works this to mid on and denies the single this time.
On middle, tucked to square leg.
An appeal for caught behind but turned down. On a length and around off, Kane looks to pad this one away but it takes the pad and goes to Rizwan. They go up in appeal but the umpire says no.
On off, blocked.
On a length and on off, well kept out by Williamson.

5 WIDES. Too short and this will be a wide and a boundary. This one is around off, Henry leaves it alone because it is too short, Rizwan tries to hop to grab this one but misses. The ball runs away to the third man fence. Wided too, by the umpire.
Bouncer on middle, Henry sits under this one.
Another bouncer on middle and off, HN ducks under this one.

FOUR! Not what Nicholls was looking to do, but as long as the boundaries come, he won't care. On a shorter length on middle, Henry moves to the leg side and looks to slash this one away but the ball takes the top edge and goes over the keeper's head into the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Bouncer on middle, HN sits this one out.
Another bouncer on off, HN leaves it alone. Also, Naseem has overstepped. Will be a No Ball.
Full and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
On off, solid in defense, is Henry.
On off, guided to the gully fielder.
On a length and on middle, tucked to the square leg region.
On off, worked to the mid on region for a quick run.
Short of a length and around off, pulled through mid-wicket for another single.
On off, blocked out well. 'No' is the call for the single, by Kane.
On off, blocked to the leg side.
On a length and outside off, HN leaves this one alone.
Outside off, left alone again.

On a length and around off, Williamson looked to block this one out but the ball takes the outside edge and goes through the gully region and the batters collect three runs. This also brings up the 50-run partnership between these two. The Kiwis needed this and these both have done well to deliver so far.
On middle, nudged to the deep square leg region for a brace.
Full ball on middle, Kane, again clips this one through square leg for a couple of runs.
On middle, nudged to the leg side. 7 runs off Masood's first over.
Floated on off, well kept out.
Loopy and around off, HN blocks this one out.
Same delivery as the last ball, Henry blocks it out again.
Goes short and outside off this time, Nicholls rocks back and punches this one through covers to pick up three runs.
Flighted on off, Kane is solid in his defense.
FOUR! Ends the over on a good note, does Kane! Flighted and around off, Williamson skips down the track and lofts this one over the fielder at mid on and the ball runs away to the ropes.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length and around off, Henry slashes this one through point to pick up a single.
FOUR! Williamson does not miss out on these! Slightly shorter and around off, Kane swivel-pulls this one through the diving fielder at mid-wicket and the ball runs away to the ropes.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Kane and he moves to 37 now. Changes the length this time and bowls a full ball on middle, Williamson tucks this one through the mid-wicket region to find the ropes. KW pouncing on Shan here.
Outside off, Kane slashes this one to deep point for a single.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
Floated on off, pushed to covers.
Flighted and on middle, Kane pushes this back to the bowler.
Loopy and around off, Kane works this one through mid on to rotate the strike.
Flighted on off, Henry skips down the track and pushes it back to Gohar.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
Flatter and on middle, punched back to Zafar. Just the one run off Gohar's second over.
Flatter and on middle, worked to the leg side for one.
Short and outside off, Nicholls cuts this one to deep point for a single.
Floated on off, Kane works this to covers.
On off, blocked out.

IN THE AIR..SHORT! They could have got the big wicket of Kane Williamson but it was not meant to be. Flatter and on off, Williamson looks to tuck this one away to the leg side but it comes off the lower part of the blade and goes towards the fielder at mid-wicket but the ball lands short of the man there.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2!
Shortish and outside off, Henry cuts but finds point there.
FOUR! This one is cut away wide. A bit of a loosener. Short and outside off, Henry cuts it through backward point and obtains a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
In the channel outside off, Henry shoulders arms.
Full and outside off from Mohammad, Nicholls leaves it alone again.
Good length ball outside off, defended to the leg side.
Fullish and on middle, tucked to short mid-wicket. The fielder there misfields, conceding a single. And that brings up the 150 for New Zealand.
Shortish and around off, Henry jumps and keeps it out.
Around off, Nicholls taps it back to the bowler.
Short and outside off, Henry Nicholls looks to cut but ends up chopping it to the keeper, off his bottom part of bat.
Good length ball around off, defended to mid on. A 'no' follows.
Short and outside off, HN hops and punches that between backward point and cover-point. Takes two runs.
Good length ball outside off, Kane defends it.
Shortish and outside the off pole, Williamson rocks back and pulls it in front of square on the on side. Mid-wicket gives chase and keeps it out. Three taken though.
Good length ball angled into the off pole line, defended to the off side. A 'no' from Henry follows.

An appeal for a caught behind but not given. Hmm.... Pakistan do not opt to review that. There was some sound there. Good length ball just outside the off pole line, Henry stands tall and looks to defend. But he misses and there is some sound as the ball goes past his outside edge and Rizwan takes it. Maybe the boot just scraped the pitch there.
Good length ball angled into the off pole line, blocked.
Fullish and around off, tapped to short mid-wicket for a quick single.
FOUR! Straying this time. Too good for that. On the pads of Henry Nicholls, he tickles it down to the fine leg boundary with ease. Too easy for Nicholls there.
Good length ball around off, defended to the off side.
Full and around the off pole, Henry pushes it straight back. It hits the stumps at the other end and deflects to mid on. New Zealand sneak in a single.
Good length ball outside off, left alone. Kane is a difficult batsman to bowl to.
Very full and outside off, jammed out to mid on. Williamson says 'no' to the single.
Full and outside off, Kane Williamson gets across and blocks it out.
Good length ball outside off, Henry gets across and taps it to the leg side. Says 'no' to his captain, for a single.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Good length ball outside off, Nicholls moves across and defends it out to mid on. Rizwan says 'bowling, well bowled'.
Length delivery around the off pole line, defensively nudged to short mid-wicket. A 'no' follows again.
Outside off, left alone.
Abbas angles in a length ball on the off pole line, Henry Nicholls looks to tuck it on the leg side but misses and it comes off his pads, and goes to the on side.
Length ball outside off, Kane gets across and fends it out. Says no to Henry for a single.

EDGED AND FOUR! Gets the outside edge.... but it goes flying through. Length delivery outside off, Kane looks to defend but gets an outside edge there. Squared him up. It goes in the gap between slips and gully and to the third man region for a boundary. They need to put an extra fielder there, Pakistan.
